The IPSA to data.parliament (commons) concordance table

Source: R/data_ipsa_commons.R
ipsa_commons.Rd

A concordance table between the UK Independent Parliamentary Standards Authority (IPSA) and the UK data.parliament Members' Name Data Platform, where the data.parliament member_id is matched to the IPSA data.

data("ipsa_commons")

Format

A data frame with 950 observations on the following 32 variables.

member_id

a character vector

dods_id

a character vector

pims_id

a character vector

clerks_id

a character vector

display_as

a character vector, the data.parliament preferred name. commons_short is based on this

list_as

a character vector

full_title

a character vector

laying_minister_name

a character vector

date_of_birth

a POSIXct

date_of_death

a POSIXct

gender

a character vector

house

a character vector

member_from

a character vector, the data.parliament constituency

house_start_date

a POSIXct

house_end_date

a Date

party_id

a character vector

party_text

a character vector

current_status_id

a character vector

current_status_is_active

a character vector

current_status_name

a character vector

current_status_reason

a character vector

current_status_start_date

a POSIXct

commons_short

a character vector used for name matching between datasets, derived from display_as

mps_name

The IPSA name, a character vector

mps_constituency

The IPSA constituency, a character vector

current_role

a character vector

ipsa_name

the IPSA name, duplicates mps_name, character

dp_name

data.parliament name, duplicates display_as, character

Examples

  data(ipsa_commons)
